The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Clive Lloyd to join Windies squad

 Clive Lloyd

Port of Spain: Former captain Clive Lloyd will join the West Indies cricket team in India to share his vast experience with Brian Lara and Co. During the upcoming ICC Champions Trophy. 

Lloyd will serve the dual purpose of West Indies Cricket Board (WICB) representative to explore opportunities for additional games next year as well as to make his vast experience available, WICB president Ken Gordon said. 

 He has agreed to make himself accessible to 

 the captain, coach and manager to assist in any way which 

 will build morale, strengthen the teams performance 

 and encourage a stronger culture of professionalism and 

 discipline, Gordon was quoted as saying by the a Trinidad 

 daily on Tuesday. The WICB president said Lloyds experience 

 will help the team in the event. (PTI) 




